\pard\plain \tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_H::2>Strictly following the instructions below, please enhance the dialogue by adding action tags and dialogue tags as necessary. If additional or modified narrative is needed to enhance the scene, you have the freedom to do so as long as you don't modify or exclude any of dialogue I provided below.}{\f1\fs26\i1\cf4  }
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\i1\cf4 In order to maintain consistency, I will typically, if not always include two sections when requesting for you to write a scene.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 One Section will include detailed instructions and will be titled "Adhere to these Instructions and Guidelines when creating this part of the scene:" }
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 The other section will include the components of the scene to be created. This will include some or all of the following items; dialogue, instructions, narrative. This section will be titled "Screen Components:"}
